// An `extension def m` inside `given g: TC[T] with` is emitted prefixed `g_m`, but a call `recv.m(a)`
// refers to the bare `m` (via __methodOrExt__). With 2+ instances there is no single `m`; synthesise a
// bare `m` DISPATCHER that type-tests the receiver tag and forwards to the matching `g_m`. One entry per
// given-body ext method: (mname, (typeHead, (implName, arity))), in source order. Emitted AFTER userDefs.
